27static const int ADJUST_ROW_NUMBER_SKIP = 2;
28
29DetectionResult::DetectionResult(const BarcodeMetadata& barcodeMetadata, const Nullable<BoundingBox>& boundingBox) :
30 _barcodeMetadata(barcodeMetadata),
31 _detectionResultColumns(barcodeMetadata.columnCount() + 2),
32 _boundingBox(boundingBox)
33{
34}
35
36void
37DetectionResult::init(const BarcodeMetadata& barcodeMetadata, const Nullable<BoundingBox>& boundingBox)
38{
39 _barcodeMetadata = barcodeMetadata;
40 _boundingBox = boundingBox;
41 _detectionResultColumns.resize(barcodeMetadata.columnCount() + 2);
42 std::fill(_detectionResultColumns.begin(), _detectionResultColumns.end(), nullptr);
43}
44
45static void AdjustIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>& detectionResultColumn, const BarcodeMetadata& barcodeMetadata)
46{
47 if (detectionResultColumn != nullptr) {
48 detectionResultColumn.value().adjustCompleteIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(barcodeMetadata);
49 }
50}
51
52static void AdjustRowNumbersFromBothRI(std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>>& detectionResultColumns)
53{
54 if (detectionResultColumns.front() == nullptr || detectionResultColumns.back() == nullptr) {
55 return;
56 }
57 auto& LRIcodewords = detectionResultColumns.front().value().allCodewords();
58 auto& RRIcodewords = detectionResultColumns.back().value().allCodewords();
59 for (size_t codewordsRow = 0; codewordsRow < LRIcodewords.size(); codewordsRow++) {
60 if (LRIcodewords[codewordsRow] != nullptr && RRIcodewords[codewordsRow] != nullptr &&
61 LRIcodewords[codewordsRow].value().rowNumber() == RRIcodewords[codewordsRow].value().rowNumber()) {
62 auto lastColumn = detectionResultColumns.end() - 1;
63 for (auto columnIter = detectionResultColumns.begin() + 1; columnIter != lastColumn; ++columnIter) {
64 if (!columnIter->hasValue()) {
65 continue;
66 }
67 auto& codeword = columnIter->value().allCodewords()[codewordsRow];
68 if (codeword != nullptr) {
69 codeword.value().setRowNumber(LRIcodewords[codewordsRow].value().rowNumber());
70 if (!codeword.value().hasValidRowNumber()) {
71 columnIter->value().allCodewords()[codewordsRow] = nullptr;
72 }
73 }
74 }
75 }
76 }
77}
78
79static int AdjustRowNumberIfValid(int rowIndicatorRowNumber, int invalidRowCounts, Codeword& codeword) {
80 if (!codeword.hasValidRowNumber()) {
81 if (codeword.isValidRowNumber(rowIndicatorRowNumber)) {
82 codeword.setRowNumber(rowIndicatorRowNumber);
83 invalidRowCounts = 0;
84 }
85 else {
86 ++invalidRowCounts;
87 }
88 }
89 return invalidRowCounts;
90}
91
92static int AdjustRowNumbersFromLRI(std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>>& detectionResultColumns) {
93 if (detectionResultColumns.front() == nullptr) {
94 return 0;
95 }
96 int unadjustedCount = 0;
97 auto& codewords = detectionResultColumns.front().value().allCodewords();
98 for (size_t codewordsRow = 0; codewordsRow < codewords.size(); codewordsRow++) {
99 if (codewords[codewordsRow] == nullptr) {
100 continue;
101 }
102 int rowIndicatorRowNumber = codewords[codewordsRow].value().rowNumber();
103 int invalidRowCounts = 0;
104 auto lastColumn = detectionResultColumns.end() - 1;
105 for (auto columnIter = detectionResultColumns.begin() + 1; columnIter != lastColumn && invalidRowCounts < ADJUST_ROW_NUMBER_SKIP; ++columnIter) {
106 if (!columnIter->hasValue()) {
107 continue;
108 }
109 auto& codeword = columnIter->value().allCodewords()[codewordsRow];
110 if (codeword != nullptr) {
111 invalidRowCounts = AdjustRowNumberIfValid(rowIndicatorRowNumber, invalidRowCounts, codeword.value());
112 if (!codeword.value().hasValidRowNumber()) {
113 unadjustedCount++;
114 }
115 }
116 }
117 }
118 return unadjustedCount;
119}
120
121static int AdjustRowNumbersFromRRI(std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>>& detectionResultColumns) {
122 if (detectionResultColumns.back() == nullptr) {
123 return 0;
124 }
125 int unadjustedCount = 0;
126 auto& codewords = detectionResultColumns.back().value().allCodewords();
127 for (size_t codewordsRow = 0; codewordsRow < codewords.size(); codewordsRow++) {
128 if (codewords[codewordsRow] == nullptr) {
129 continue;
130 }
131 int rowIndicatorRowNumber = codewords[codewordsRow].value().rowNumber();
132 int invalidRowCounts = 0;
133 auto lastColumn = detectionResultColumns.end() - 1;
134 for (auto columnIter = detectionResultColumns.begin() + 1; columnIter != lastColumn && invalidRowCounts < ADJUST_ROW_NUMBER_SKIP; ++columnIter) {
135 if (!columnIter->hasValue()) {
136 continue;
137 }
138 auto& codeword = columnIter->value().allCodewords()[codewordsRow];
139 if (codeword != nullptr) {
140 invalidRowCounts = AdjustRowNumberIfValid(rowIndicatorRowNumber, invalidRowCounts, codeword.value());
141 if (!codeword.value().hasValidRowNumber()) {
142 unadjustedCount++;
143 }
144 }
145 }
146 }
147 return unadjustedCount;
148}
149
150
151static int AdjustRowNumbersByRow(std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>>& detectionResultColumns) {
152 AdjustRowNumbersFromBothRI(detectionResultColumns);
153 // TODO we should only do full row adjustments if row numbers of left and right row indicator column match.
154 // Maybe it's even better to calculated the height (in codeword rows) and divide it by the number of barcode
155 // rows. This, together with the LRI and RRI row numbers should allow us to get a good estimate where a row
156 // number starts and ends.
157 int unadjustedCount = AdjustRowNumbersFromLRI(detectionResultColumns);
158 return unadjustedCount + AdjustRowNumbersFromRRI(detectionResultColumns);
159}
160
161
162/**
163* @return true, if row number was adjusted, false otherwise
164*/
165static bool AdjustRowNumber(Nullable<Codeword>& codeword, const Nullable<Codeword>& otherCodeword) {
166 if (codeword != nullptr && otherCodeword != nullptr
167 && otherCodeword.value().hasValidRowNumber() && otherCodeword.value().bucket() == codeword.value().bucket()) {
168 codeword.value().setRowNumber(otherCodeword.value().rowNumber());
169 return true;
170 }
171 return false;
172}
173
174static void AdjustRowNumbers(const std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>>& detectionResultColumns, int barcodeColumn, int codewordsRow, std::vector<Nullable<Codeword>>& codewords) {
175 auto& codeword = codewords[codewordsRow];
176 auto& previousColumnCodewords = detectionResultColumns[barcodeColumn - 1].value().allCodewords();
177 auto& nextColumnCodewords = detectionResultColumns[barcodeColumn + 1] != nullptr ? detectionResultColumns[barcodeColumn + 1].value().allCodewords() : previousColumnCodewords;
178
179 std::array<Nullable<Codeword>, 14> otherCodewords;
180
181 otherCodewords[2] = previousColumnCodewords[codewordsRow];
182 otherCodewords[3] = nextColumnCodewords[codewordsRow];
183
184 if (codewordsRow > 0) {
185 otherCodewords[0] = codewords[codewordsRow - 1];
186 otherCodewords[4] = previousColumnCodewords[codewordsRow - 1];
187 otherCodewords[5] = nextColumnCodewords[codewordsRow - 1];
188 }
189 if (codewordsRow > 1) {
190 otherCodewords[8] = codewords[codewordsRow - 2];
191 otherCodewords[10] = previousColumnCodewords[codewordsRow - 2];
192 otherCodewords[11] = nextColumnCodewords[codewordsRow - 2];
193 }
194 if (codewordsRow < (int)codewords.size() - 1) {
195 otherCodewords[1] = codewords[codewordsRow + 1];
196 otherCodewords[6] = previousColumnCodewords[codewordsRow + 1];
197 otherCodewords[7] = nextColumnCodewords[codewordsRow + 1];
198 }
199 if (codewordsRow < (int)codewords.size() - 2) {
200 otherCodewords[9] = codewords[codewordsRow + 2];
201 otherCodewords[12] = previousColumnCodewords[codewordsRow + 2];
202 otherCodewords[13] = nextColumnCodewords[codewordsRow + 2];
203 }
204 for (const auto& otherCodeword : otherCodewords) {
205 if (AdjustRowNumber(codeword, otherCodeword)) {
206 return;
207 }
208 }
209}
210
211
212// TODO ensure that no detected codewords with unknown row number are left
213// we should be able to estimate the row height and use it as a hint for the row number
214// we should also fill the rows top to bottom and bottom to top
215/**
216* @return number of codewords which don't have a valid row number. Note that the count is not accurate as codewords
217* will be counted several times. It just serves as an indicator to see when we can stop adjusting row numbers
218*/
219static int AdjustRowNumbers(std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>>& detectionResultColumns) {
220 int unadjustedCount = AdjustRowNumbersByRow(detectionResultColumns);
221 if (unadjustedCount == 0) {
222 return 0;
223 }
224 for (int barcodeColumn = 1; barcodeColumn < (int)detectionResultColumns.size() - 1; barcodeColumn++) {
225 if (detectionResultColumns[barcodeColumn] == nullptr) {
226 continue;
227 }
228 auto& codewords = detectionResultColumns[barcodeColumn].value().allCodewords();
229 for (int codewordsRow = 0; codewordsRow < (int)codewords.size(); codewordsRow++) {
230 if (codewords[codewordsRow] == nullptr) {
231 continue;
232 }
233 if (!codewords[codewordsRow].value().hasValidRowNumber()) {
234 AdjustRowNumbers(detectionResultColumns, barcodeColumn, codewordsRow, codewords);
235 }
236 }
237 }
238 return unadjustedCount;
239}
240
241
242const std::vector<Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>> &
243DetectionResult::allColumns()
244{
245 AdjustIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(_detectionResultColumns.front(), _barcodeMetadata);
246 AdjustIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(_detectionResultColumns.back(), _barcodeMetadata);
247 int unadjustedCodewordCount = CodewordDecoder::MAX_CODEWORDS_IN_BARCODE;
248 int previousUnadjustedCount;
249 do {
250 previousUnadjustedCount = unadjustedCodewordCount;
251 unadjustedCodewordCount = AdjustRowNumbers(_detectionResultColumns);
252 } while (unadjustedCodewordCount > 0 && unadjustedCodewordCount < previousUnadjustedCount);
253 return _detectionResultColumns;
254}
